# PIC16F877A Password Authentication System

This project implements a simple password authentication system using the **PIC16F877A** microcontroller, a **4×3 matrix keypad**, and a **16×2 LCD**. The user enters a 4-digit password through the keypad, and the system verifies it against a predefined password. Depending on the result, the LCD displays either **"Access Granted"** or **"Access Denied"**.

## Features

- 4-digit password authentication
- Password masking using `*`
- 4×3 matrix keypad interface
- 16×2 LCD display interface
- Displays authentication result
- Automatically resets after each attempt

## Hardware Requirements

- PIC16F877A Microcontroller
- 16×2 LCD (HD44780 Compatible)
- 4×3 Matrix Keypad
- 20 MHz Crystal Oscillator
- Two 22 pF Capacitors
- 5V Power Supply
- Breadboard and Connecting Wires

## Pin Connections

### LCD Connections

| LCD Pin | PIC16F877A Pin |
|----------|----------------|
| D0–D7    | PORTC          |
| RS       | RD0            |
| RW       | RD1            |
| EN       | RD2            |

### Keypad Connections

| Keypad Pin | PIC16F877A Pin |
|-------------|----------------|
| Column 1    | RB0 |
| Column 2    | RB1 |
| Column 3    | RB2 |
| Row 1       | RB4 |
| Row 2       | RB5 |
| Row 3       | RB6 |
| Row 4       | RB7 |

